<typeStatus box="[446,547,297,323]" pageId="13" pageNumber="95">holotype</typeStatus>
, that was not retained (
<figureCitation box="[806,922,297,323]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1768,1793]" captionTargetBox="[177,1414,306,1731]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[158,1430,306,1740]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Color photographs of Mephisto. See Table 1 for collection localities. A. Mephisto fraserbrunneri, University of Kerala DABFUK/FI/301, 64.5 mm SL. Photograph by A. Biju Kumar. B. Mephisto fraserbrunneri, University of Kerala DAB- FUK/FI/303, 64.2 mm SL. Photograph by A. Biju Kumar. C. Mephisto cf. fraserbrunneri, specimen not retained, est. 54 mm SL. Photograph by Oddgeir Alvheim. D. Mephisto cf. fraserbrunneri, specimen not retained, est. 89 mm SL. Photograph by Tom Williams. E. Mephisto albomaculosus, holotype, NSMT-P 132271, 94.4 mm SL. Photograph by Oddgeir Alvheim, from Matsuura et al. (2018), photograph reprinted with permission from the Ichthyological Society of Japan. F. Mephisto cf. albomaculosus, specimen not retained, est. 94 mm SL. Photograph by Oddgeir Alvheim, from Matsuura et al. (2018), photograph reprinted with permission from the Ichthyological Society of Japan." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3991951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3991951/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="95">Fig. 1E, F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
