<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="95" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,152,575]" pageId="13" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="95">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tyler" authorityYear="1966" box="[472,576,333,359]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Triacanthodidae" genus="Mephisto" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetraodontiformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="95" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[472,576,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="95">Mephisto</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with prominent white, rounded (more-or-less circular to oval) markings that are up to as large as the pupil diameter and located on the lower half of the body (
<figureCitation box="[1065,1182,369,395]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1768,1793]" captionTargetBox="[177,1414,306,1731]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[158,1430,306,1740]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Color photographs of Mephisto. See Table 1 for collection localities. A. Mephisto fraserbrunneri, University of Kerala DABFUK/FI/301, 64.5 mm SL. Photograph by A. Biju Kumar. B. Mephisto fraserbrunneri, University of Kerala DAB- FUK/FI/303, 64.2 mm SL. Photograph by A. Biju Kumar. C. Mephisto cf. fraserbrunneri, specimen not retained, est. 54 mm SL. Photograph by Oddgeir Alvheim. D. Mephisto cf. fraserbrunneri, specimen not retained, est. 89 mm SL. Photograph by Tom Williams. E. Mephisto albomaculosus, holotype, NSMT-P 132271, 94.4 mm SL. Photograph by Oddgeir Alvheim, from Matsuura et al. (2018), photograph reprinted with permission from the Ichthyological Society of Japan. F. Mephisto cf. albomaculosus, specimen not retained, est. 94 mm SL. Photograph by Oddgeir Alvheim, from Matsuura et al. (2018), photograph reprinted with permission from the Ichthyological Society of Japan." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3991951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3991951/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="95">Fig. 1E, F</figureCitation>
). Pelvic width 7.8% in SL; pelvic width into pelvic length 4.0 times; gill rakers 15; pseudobranch lamellae 16 (
<bibRefCitation author="Matsuura, K. &amp; Psomadakis, P. &amp; Tun, M. T." box="[1135,1380,405,431]" pageId="13" pageNumber="95" pagination="30 - 33" refId="ref9958" refString="Matsuura, K., Psomadakis, P. &amp; Tun, M. T. (2018) Mephisto albomaculosus, a new spikefish (Actinopterygii: Tetraodontiformes: Triacanthodidae) collected off Myanmar, Indian Ocean. Ichthyological Research, 66, 30 - 33. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 10228 - 018 - 0642 - 7" type="journal article" year="2018">
Matsuura 
<emphasis box="[1249,1305,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="95">et al.</emphasis>
, 2018
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
